      • add

        void add​(int index,
         T callback)
        Inserts the specified callback at the specified position in this chain (optional operation). Shifts the callback currently at that position (if any) and any subsequent callbacks to the right (adds one to their indices).
        Parameters:
        index - index at which the specified callback is to be inserted
        callback - callback to be inserted
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if the add operation is not supported by this chain
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the specified callback is null and this chain does not permit null callbacks
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if some property of the specified callback prevents it from being added to this chain
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the index is out of range (index < 0 || index > size())

      • remove

        T remove​(int index)
        Removes the callback at the specified position in this chain (optional operation). Shifts any subsequent callbacks to the left (subtracts one from their indices). Returns the callback that was removed from the chain.
        Parameters:
        index - the index of the callback to be removed
        Returns:
        the callback previously at the specified position
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if the remove operation is not supported by this chain
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the index is out of range (index < 0 || index >= size())

      • indexOf

        int indexOf​(T callback)
        Returns the index of the first occurrence of the specified callback in this chain, or -1 if this chain does not contain the callback. More formally, returns the lowest index i such that (o==null ? get(i)==null : o.equals(get(i))), or -1 if there is no such index.
        Parameters:
        callback - callback to search for
        Returns:
        the index of the first occurrence of the specified callback in this chain, or -1 if this chain does not contain the callback
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the specified callback is null and this chain does not permit null callbacks

      • lastIndexOf

        int lastIndexOf​(T callback)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
